cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.LG 

The paper discusses privacy-preserving consensus algorithms for decentralized information fusion in smart device networks, which involves security and privacy concerns. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with distributed computing and networked systems, which suggests categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms to improve citizens' quality of life, which suggests categories such as cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
